{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "price_divergence_sensitivity_2016",
    "description": "Test whether the ~65% economic support inversion threshold is an artifact of the \u00b120% max price divergence cap.\nBACKGROUND: Phase 2 analysis identified a \"regime shift\" at ~65% economic support where the effect of hashrate on v27 outcomes reverses direction:\n  - Below 65%: more v27 hashrate helps v27 (+15-19% effect)\n  - Above 65%: more v27 hashrate hurts v27 (-15% effect, \"inversion zone\")\n\nThis could be a fundamental dynamic OR an artifact of the \u00b120% price divergence cap hitting a ceiling at high economic support. This sweep tests the hypothesis by varying max_price_divergence across [\u00b110%, \u00b120%, \u00b130%, \u00b140%].\nEXPECTED OUTCOMES:\n  - If threshold MOVES with divergence cap: artifact of price ceiling\n  - If threshold PERSISTS across all caps: likely fundamental dynamic\n  - If threshold DISAPPEARS at higher caps: \u00b120% constraint is the cause\n\nDESIGN:\n  - max_price_divergence: 4 levels [0.10, 0.20, 0.30, 0.40]\n  - economic_split: 3 levels spanning the threshold [0.55, 0.65, 0.75]\n  - pool_committed_split: 2 levels in mid-range [0.30, 0.40]\n  - hashrate_split: 2 levels to observe the interaction [0.25, 0.50]\n  - Grid: 4 divergence \u00d7 3 economic \u00d7 2 committed \u00d7 2 hashrate = 48 scenarios\n\nNOTE: max_price_divergence is a RUNTIME flag, not a config parameter. This sweep must be run 4 times with different --max-price-divergence values. See run commands below.\nRUNTIME: 48 total scenarios (12 per divergence level) At ~35 min/scenario on lite network: ~28 hours total (~7 hours per divergence level) Recommend running all 4 divergence levels in parallel on different namespaces.\nRUN COMMANDS (run each in separate namespace or sequentially):\n# Generate scenarios (once) python tools/sweep/1_generate_targeted.py --spec specs/price_divergence_sensitivity_2016.yaml\n# Build configs (once) python tools/sweep/2_build_configs.py \\\n  --input price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/scenarios.json \\\n  --output-dir price_divergence_sensitivity_2016\n\n# Run with \u00b110% divergence cap python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n  --input price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/build_manifest.json \\\n  --results-dir price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/results_div10 \\\n  --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n  --max-price-divergence 0.10\n\n# Run with \u00b120% divergence cap (current default - control group) python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n  --input price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/build_manifest.json \\\n  --results-dir price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/results_div20 \\\n  --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n  --max-price-divergence 0.20\n\n# Run with \u00b130% divergence cap python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n  --input price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/build_manifest.json \\\n  --results-dir price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/results_div30 \\\n  --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n  --max-price-divergence 0.30\n\n# Run with \u00b140% divergence cap python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n  --input price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/build_manifest.json \\\n  --results-dir price_divergence_sensitivity_2016/results_div40 \\\n  --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2 \\\n  --max-price-divergence 0.40\n\nANALYSIS: After all runs complete, compare v27 win rates at each economic_split level across the 4 divergence caps. If the inversion at 65% disappears or shifts at higher caps, the price ceiling is the cause.\n",
